rComments: Great teacher, I enjoyed going to her classes. Definitely demanding but she grades well and I like how she makes students sign with their student numbers instead of names in order to stay objective. I recommend her class.

She is a great teacher! She is very helpful during her office hours and even will stay after class to answer any questions or to give advice regarding any assignments. She provides great context to the readings. I highly recommend her class!
Fantastic English prof. Very clear expectations, occasionally humorous and all-around great teacher. You WILL learn how to write in this class.

Super easy marker, but also the most boring class ever. Do the work, and the readings and you'll have no problem. Not a good prof and very boring. She doesn't even try to make the class interesting, just reads her powerpoints for the whole class. Unfortunately it's a mandatory class.
Awesome prof! was very clear about what she expected. Easy prof to get a high grade with! And not a lot of work

Awesome prof! She knows what she's talking about and she loves to teach. She's really clear on her expectations, and she's really helpful. She always responds to emails within 24 hours, and is always willing to meet to discuss your work/troubles. The readings were kind of boring but open you up to reading academically. Highly recommended!

I absolutely adore this prof. She's so nice and actually cares about her students. If you do the readings, you can do well. Seriously, this is the nicest lady ever and she's a great teacher, why wouldn't you take her class?

Great prof, really invested and interested in the subject matter. Engages students in discussion. Has that sweet motherly nature but doesn't stand for absentees/lazy students. Fair marker and would definitely recommend.
